The use of `zipWithIndex` on collections in a hot path can lead to performance degradation due to the allocation of `Tuple2` objects for each element. This change replaces `zipWithIndex` with a `while` loop and an explicit index counter to avoid these allocations, improving performance by reducing garbage collection pressure.

